# Override Semgrep's built-in defaults (which exclude `tests/`) so that
# our rule fixtures under semgrep/tests/ are scanned by semgrep test.
# Also re-include nothing else: we want semgrep to follow .gitignore for
# real source paths, but never let it skip our intentionally-bad fixture
# files. A single `!path` in this file flips off semgrep's default tests/
# exclusion.
!semgrep/tests/
